A local documentary is tackling difficult topics in South Africa through candid conversations with influencers. JOHANNESBURG - A local documentary is tackling difficult topics in South Africa through candid conversations with influencers. From mental health issues to black love and black tax, no topic is off-limits. The People vs The People is a sequel to The People versus Patriarchy and The People versus the Rainbow Nation. Director Lebogang Rasethaba and Mokgadi Itsweng, who is featured in the documentary, talk about black love and food.